sentences: Robert Broom Jr. (born January 18, 1961) is an American jazz guitarist, composer, and educator.
He was born and raised in New York City, then moved to Chicago, which has been his home town since 1984.
Broom was born in Harlem (1961) and raised on New York City's Upper West Side (1970s).
In 1977 he played at Carnegie Hall in a concert with Sonny Rollins and Donald Byrd.
He went to the Berklee School of Music from 1978–79, then returned to New York to pursue his career while attending Long Island University.
In the 1980s, he moved to Chicago.
He formed The Bobby Broom Trio in 1990, the Deep Blue Organ Trio with Chris Foreman and Greg Rockingham in 1999, and The Bobby Broom Organi-Sation in 2014.

In 2009 he recorded Bobby Broom Plays for Monk with its cover shot of the red wagon Monk used for the album Monk's Music.
Broom's first release of exclusively original compositions was Upper West Side Story (2012).

As an educator, Broom began his work in 1982 for Jackie McLean, Director of African American Music at Studies for the Hartt School of Music at the University of Hartford.

Over the years Broom has also been a lecturer at the American Conservatory of Music (1986–1990), Chicago Musical College — Roosevelt University (1990–1994), The Thelonious Monk Institute of Jazz (1987), DePaul University (2002–2008) and North Park University.
